From: Chinmoy Dey <chinmoy@nexthop.ai>
Date: Mon, 16 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] Make leak detection discoverable by navigation

The standalone DMTF leak-detection handlers (patch 0004) register the
LeakDetection / LeakDetectorCollection / LeakDetector routes, but the
resources were not reachable by navigating the resource tree: neither
the Chassis resource nor the ThermalSubsystem resource advertised a
link to them.

Add the standard navigation links, as upstream does for every other
child resource, so the leak-detection tree is discoverable like a normal
Redfish resource. Both link targets are properties already defined in the
bundled schemas (Chassis.LeakDetectors since Chassis v1.26.0,
ThermalSubsystem.LeakDetection), so the responses remain schema-valid
under additionalProperties:false.

 * chassis.hpp: advertise the canonical Chassis-level LeakDetectors
   collection (/redfish/v1/Chassis/<id>/LeakDetectors).
 * thermal_subsystem.hpp: advertise the deprecated nested LeakDetection
   resource (/redfish/v1/Chassis/<id>/ThermalSubsystem/LeakDetection).

This patch only adds link properties to existing handlers; it adds no
new routes (those come from patch 0004).
---
 redfish-core/lib/chassis.hpp           | 3 +++
 redfish-core/lib/thermal_subsystem.hpp | 4 ++++
 2 files changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/redfish-core/lib/chassis.hpp b/redfish-core/lib/chassis.hpp
--- a/redfish-core/lib/chassis.hpp
+++ b/redfish-core/lib/chassis.hpp
@@ -453,4 +453,7 @@
     // SensorCollection
     asyncResp->res.jsonValue["Sensors"]["@odata.id"] =
         boost::urls::format("/redfish/v1/Chassis/{}/Sensors", chassisId);
+
+    asyncResp->res.jsonValue["LeakDetectors"]["@odata.id"] =
+        boost::urls::format("/redfish/v1/Chassis/{}/LeakDetectors", chassisId);
     asyncResp->res.jsonValue["Status"]["State"] = resource::State::Enabled;
diff --git a/redfish-core/lib/thermal_subsystem.hpp b/redfish-core/lib/thermal_subsystem.hpp
--- a/redfish-core/lib/thermal_subsystem.hpp
+++ b/redfish-core/lib/thermal_subsystem.hpp
@@ -53,6 +53,10 @@
     asyncResp->res.jsonValue["ThermalMetrics"]["@odata.id"] =
         boost::urls::format(
             "/redfish/v1/Chassis/{}/ThermalSubsystem/ThermalMetrics",
             chassisId);
+
+    asyncResp->res.jsonValue["LeakDetection"]["@odata.id"] =
+        boost::urls::format(
+            "/redfish/v1/Chassis/{}/ThermalSubsystem/LeakDetection", chassisId);

     asyncResp->res.jsonValue["Status"]["State"] = resource::State::Enabled;
